docs.lead_paragraph: The New York Philharmonic will present a concert performance of "Oklahoma!" on March 26 at Philharmonic Hall for the benefit of the orchestra's pension fund. The performance is celebrating the 25th anniversary of the musical composed and written by Richard Rodgers and Oscar Hammerstein 2d. It will be the first time the work has been given in a concert version.

headline.main: 'Oklahoma!' to Be Presented In Concert at Philharmonic
